#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:1
msgid "Cache-DiT Acceleration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:3
msgid ""
"SGLang integrates [Cache-DiT](https://github.com/vipshop/cache-dit), a "
"caching acceleration engine for Diffusion Transformers (DiT), to achieve up "
"to **1.69x inference speedup** with minimal quality loss."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:5
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:7
msgid ""
"**Cache-DiT** uses intelligent caching strategies to skip redundant "
"computation in the denoising loop:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:9
msgid ""
"**DBCache (Dual Block Cache)**: Dynamically decides when to cache "
"transformer blocks based on residual differences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:10
msgid ""
"**TaylorSeer**: Uses Taylor expansion for calibration to optimize caching "
"decisions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:11
msgid ""
"**SCM (Step Computation Masking)**: Step-level caching control for "
"additional speedup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:13
msgid "Basic Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:15
msgid ""
"Enable Cache-DiT by exporting the environment variable and using `sglang "
"generate` or `sglang serve` :"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:17
msgid ""
"SGLANG_CACHE_DIT_ENABLED=true \\\n"
"sglang generate --model-path Qwen/Qwen-Image \\\n"
"    --prompt \"A beautiful sunset over the mountains\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:23
msgid "Diffusers Backend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:25
msgid ""
"Cache-DiT supports loading acceleration configs from a custom YAML file. For "
"diffusers pipelines (`diffusers` backend), pass the YAML/JSON path via `--"
"cache-dit-config`. This flow requires cache-dit >= 1.2.0 (`cache_dit."
"load_configs`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:29
msgid "Single GPU inference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:31
msgid "Define a `cache.yaml` file that contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:33
msgid ""
"cache_config:\n"
"  max_warmup_steps: 8\n"
"  warmup_interval: 2\n"
"  max_cached_steps: -1\n"
"  max_continuous_cached_steps: 2\n"
"  Fn_compute_blocks: 1\n"
"  Bn_compute_blocks: 0\n"
"  residual_diff_threshold: 0.12\n"
"  enable_taylorseer: true\n"
"  taylorseer_order: 1\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:46
msgid "Then apply the config with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:48
msgid ""
"sglang generate \\\n"
"  --backend diffusers \\\n"
"  --model-path Qwen/Qwen-Image \\\n"
"  --cache-dit-config cache.yaml \\\n"
"  --prompt \"A beautiful sunset over the mountains\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:56
msgid "Distributed inference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:58
msgid "1D Parallelism"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:60
msgid ""
"Define a parallelism only config yaml `parallel.yaml` file that contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:62
msgid ""
"parallelism_config:\n"
"  ulysses_size: auto\n"
"  parallel_kwargs:\n"
"    attention_backend: native\n"
"    extra_parallel_modules: [\"text_encoder\", \"vae\"]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:70
msgid ""
"Then, apply the distributed inference acceleration config from yaml. "
"`ulysses_size: auto` means that cache-dit will auto detect the `world_size` "
"as the ulysses_size. Otherwise, you should manually set it as specific int "
"number, e.g, 4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:72
msgid ""
"Then apply the distributed config with: (Note: please add `--num-gpus N` to "
"specify the number of gpus for distributed inference)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:74
msgid ""
"sglang generate \\\n"
"  --backend diffusers \\\n"
"  --num-gpus 4 \\\n"
"  --model-path Qwen/Qwen-Image \\\n"
"  --cache-dit-config parallel.yaml \\\n"
"  --prompt \"A futuristic cityscape at sunset\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:83
msgid "2D Parallelism"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:85
msgid ""
"You can also define a 2D parallelism config yaml `parallel_2d.yaml` file "
"that contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:87
msgid ""
"parallelism_config:\n"
"  ulysses_size: auto\n"
"  tp_size: 2\n"
"  parallel_kwargs:\n"
"    attention_backend: native\n"
"    extra_parallel_modules: [\"text_encoder\", \"vae\"]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:95
msgid ""
"Then, apply the 2D parallelism config from yaml. Here `tp_size: 2` means "
"using tensor parallelism with size 2. The `ulysses_size: auto` means that "
"cache-dit will auto detect the `world_size // tp_size` as the ulysses_size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:97
msgid "3D Parallelism"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:99
msgid ""
"You can also define a 3D parallelism config yaml `parallel_3d.yaml` file "
"that contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:101
msgid ""
"parallelism_config:\n"
"  ulysses_size: 2\n"
"  ring_size: 2\n"
"  tp_size: 2\n"
"  parallel_kwargs:\n"
"    attention_backend: native\n"
"    extra_parallel_modules: [\"text_encoder\", \"vae\"]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:110
msgid ""
"Then, apply the 3D parallelism config from yaml. Here `ulysses_size: 2`, "
"`ring_size: 2`, `tp_size: 2` means using ulysses parallelism with size 2, "
"ring parallelism with size 2 and tensor parallelism with size 2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:112
msgid "Hybrid Cache and Parallelism"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:114
msgid ""
"Define a hybrid cache and parallel acceleration config yaml `hybrid.yaml` "
"file that contains:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:116
msgid ""
"cache_config:\n"
"  max_warmup_steps: 8\n"
"  warmup_interval: 2\n"
"  max_cached_steps: -1\n"
"  max_continuous_cached_steps: 2\n"
"  Fn_compute_blocks: 1\n"
"  Bn_compute_blocks: 0\n"
"  residual_diff_threshold: 0.12\n"
"  enable_taylorseer: true\n"
"  taylorseer_order: 1\n"
"parallelism_config:\n"
"  ulysses_size: auto\n"
"  parallel_kwargs:\n"
"    attention_backend: native\n"
"    extra_parallel_modules: [\"text_encoder\", \"vae\"]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:134
msgid ""
"Then, apply the hybrid cache and parallel acceleration config from yaml."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/performance/cache/cache_dit.md:136
msgid ""
"sglang generate \\\n"
"  --backend diffusers \\\n"
"  --num-gpus 4 \\\n"
"  --model-path Qwen/Qwen-Image \\\n"
"  --cache-dit-config hybrid.yaml \\\n"
"  --prompt \"A beautiful sunset over the mountains\"\n"
msgstr ""

